title: Photos Biologists fly drone to track health of endangered orcas
text:
Photos: Biologists fly drone to track health of endangered orcas 
KATU 2 Thursday 22nd October, 2015 
SEATTLE (AP) - Federal biologists flying a drone have taken thousands of rich images of endangered Puget Sound orcas showing the whales are in good condition this year and that several appear to be pregnant.The drone flights over Washington's San Juan Islands captured striking photographs of all 81 members of the small population of orcas that spend much of their time in the state's inland waters.
